The paper discusses the use of game theory to analyze cyber deception strategies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of signaling game models, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of evidence-based strategies and dynamic risk mitigation, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of Bayesian game models for defensive deception, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE).
